# cost-onprem-chart — prefer local chart

## Default interpretation

When the user asks to **install**, **upgrade**, or **deploy** **cost-onprem** / **cost-onprem-chart** (including on a new leased cluster), use the **local chart** in **`submodules/cost-onprem-chart/cost-onprem`**, not the published Helm repo (`insights-onprem.github.io/cost-onprem-chart`).

**User preference (workspace):** local chart over upstream unless they explicitly ask for the Helm repo / a pinned upstream version.

## Preferred command

From **`submodules/cost-onprem-chart`**:

```bash
cd submodules/cost-onprem-chart
USE_LOCAL_CHART=true ./scripts/install-helm-chart.sh
```

The install script defaults to `USE_LOCAL_CHART=false`; **always set `USE_LOCAL_CHART=true`** for this workspace unless the user opts into upstream.

## Why local (typical)

Published stable releases (e.g. **0.2.19**) can lag **`main`** — missing templates such as UI nginx `location /rbac/` and Envoy `/api/rbac/` needed for FLPATH-4164 / RBAC MFE work.

## After install / upgrade

1. `./scripts/install-helm-chart.sh health`
2. If UI nginx ConfigMap changed: `oc rollout restart deployment/cost-onprem-ui -n cost-onprem` (no ConfigMap checksum on the Deployment; `subPath` mounts need a pod restart)
3. Keycloak JWT check: `bash .cursor/skills/cost-onprem-chart-install/scripts/keycloak-fix-org-jwt-claims.sh verify` (then `fix` if needed)

## Do not use by default

| Approach | When |
| -------- | ---- |
| `./scripts/install-helm-chart.sh` alone | Uses upstream Helm repo — only if user explicitly wants published chart |
| `CHART_VERSION=0.2.x` without `USE_LOCAL_CHART=true` | Pins upstream, not local submodule |

